FBIS4-57159 "drlat093_m_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 Brazil Officials on Army Role, Federal Police Demands Officials on Army Role, Federal Police Demands PY1205133494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 1000 GMT 12 May 94 PY1205133494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Portuguese BFN [Text] Federal Administration Secretary Romildo Canhim has said there is no Army intervention in the Federal Police because the military are not fulfilling the functions of federal policemen, like controlling and issuing passports. Civil Household Chief Henrique Hargreaves said government action is not against the strike, but against disorder and indiscipline. Hargreaves added that their demand for salary parity with those of civil policemen is illegal.
